@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@TOC Main
@{PARI 4}
At the beginning of the year 1996, I purchased a CDRom drive. As I wanted to
play audio CDs (CDDA) I started to search for CDplayers on Aminet.@{PAR}
But after some tries with a lot of players, none of these convinced me, mainly
because there was no player that can do test for diskchange by themselves as
I own an Apollo SCSI2 controller that don't recognize diskchange interrupts.@{PAR}
So I decided to program a player with a lot of features and here is
@{BOLD "OptyCDPlayer"}!@{PAR}
@{PAR}
This CD player is not finally a simple player. Of course you have all the
functionality of a real CD player but with some special things like Title
edition, Multiple program edition, and CD SAMPLING!@{PAR}
@{PAR}
This program is copyrighted 1996 by Stéphane Barbaray.@{PAR}
It is EMailWare, so just send me E-Mail to give hellos and feedbacks about
this program and all will be fine...@{PAR}
If your CD drive can do sampling and it is not on the CD sampler list, just
tell it to me !@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Legal "Legal stuff"
@TOC Main
@{PARI 4}
OptyCDPlayer is copyrighted freeware. It may be distributed freely as long as
no modifications are made to the executable and this document. A nominal fee
may be asked to cover distribution costs.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
OptyCDPlayer may not be used for any commercial purposes or included with any
commercial product without the written permission of the author.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
No responsibilities are taken for damaged CDs, CDROM drives, Amigas or any
other components or data involved while using OptyCDPlayer.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Although I've done some beta testing I can't guarantee that OptyCDPlayer will
not crash! If you find any bugs, let me know.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Copying is prohibited with some types of CDs so don't copy them!@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"
@TOC Main
@{UNDERLINED "Computer"}:@{PAR}
Any Amiga 68020+ running Kickstart/Workbench 2.04 or greater.@{PAR}
@{UNDERLINED "Hardware"}:@{PAR}
A CD-Rom drive.@{PAR}
@{UNDERLINED "Software"}:@{PAR}
You need @{"MUI" LINK MUI} 3.1 or later. See @{"MUI" LINK MUI} part in this
document (Hello Stefan!).@{PAR}
You need NList.mcc and NListView.mcc (partially included in the distribution).@{PAR}
@{"Play16" LINK Play16} 1.5+ for playing sample, available on Aminet in mus/play folder.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Just copy the main program where you want.@{PAR}
The catalog directory must be in the directory where you have put the main
program or just place it in "sys:locale/".@{PAR}
The other directories supplied with this program MUST be in the same directory
of the program.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Just dearchiving the distribution where you want OptyCDPlayer to be placed
will be fine too...@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Configuration "Configuration"
@TOC Main
Configuration is made thru the @{"preferences" LINK PREFS} page.@{PAR}
You must select Prefs/Save from the menu to save them.@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GUI "GUI description"
@TOC Main
@{"Player page"		LINK PLAYER}	@{PAR}
@{"Title page"		LINK TITLE}	@{PAR}
@{"Programs page"	LINK PROGRAMS}	@{PAR}
@{"Sampler page"	LINK SAMPLER}	@{PAR}
@{"Preferences page"	LINK PREFS}	@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE PLAYER "Player page"
@TOC GUI
@{PARI 4}
It contains all the common commands of a real CD player. The list at the right
contains the title that you affected for each track. Double-clicking on a
title will play this title.@{PAR}
The volume sub-panel is the software control of the volume. It may @{BOLD "not"} work
with some exotic drives !@{PAR}
A-B repeat mode has been made to repeat a portion of a track from A to B.@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE TITLE "Title page"
@TOC GUI
@{PARI 4}
This panel is very easy to understand: all you will have to do is to insert
the CD you want to edit, to modify each title, and to save in one of the
proposed format when you have finished. The buttons in the second column are
for format conversion. 'Merge DB' button permit to merge a database to the
program database. 'DB Viewer' will open a listtree sub-window that show the
content of the actual database.@{PAR}@{PARI 0}

@{UNDERLINED "NOTE"}:@{PAR}
The files saved are compatible with CD Descriptions of MCDPlayer and others,
@{BOLD "excepted"} when YACDP option is activated!@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE PROGRAMS "Programs page"
@TOC GUI
@{PARI 4}
This panel is based on Drag&Drop facilities of MUI3. As with the @{"title page" LINK TITLE},
you must have a CD to edit your programs. You can have 8+1 programs for each
CDs.@{PAR}
The first program is for automatic playing at CD insertion. You can play a
track multiple time in a program.@{PAR}
To add an entry, just drag one item from the source to the destination.@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE SAMPLER "Sampler page"
@TOC GUI
To save a part of your CD:@{PAR}
@{PARI -3}
@{LINDENT 3}
1) Insert the CD@{PAR}
2) Choose the TRACK number@{PAR}
3) Choose the number of seconds the sampling must START@{PAR}
4) Choose the number of seconds for the sampling DURATION@{PAR}
5) Select the file to save (required)@{PAR}
6) Select the type of drive if not already done@{PAR}
7) Select your prefered format,channel,frequency@{PAR}
8) Click on save or Save&Play (Save THEN play)@{PAR}
@{PARI 0}
@{LINDENT 0}
@{PAR}
The play button is only for an already saved sample. If the sample is in RAW
format you @{BOLD "MUST"} adjust correctly format, channel, frequency because Play16
don't know anything about the sample that you ask for replaying!@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "* WARNING *"}@{PAR}
This functionality uses SCSI commands that are not documented, this may or may
not work with your CD drive. Use it at your own risk. Don't forget that
Copying is prohibited with some types of CDs.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Never use Amiga audio mode if you are low-powered!!!@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
@{UNDERLINED "Reported to work on:			TYPE:			MODE:"}
Toshiba XM series (excepted SCSI1)	(SCSI)			TOSHIBA
Toshiba XM series 			(ATAPI)			ATAPI
Sony CDU 541,561,8002,8003,55S,...	(SCSI)			SONY
Sony CDU 33A,...			(ATAPI)			ATAPI
Apple CD300,CD600			(SCSI)			SONY
Pioneer DR-124X				(ATAPI)			SONY
IBM PS/2 CD drives			(SCSI)			TOSHIBA
Hitachi CDR				(ATAPI)			ATAPI
NEC CD drives				(ATAPI)			ATAPI
Chinon CDS-535				(SCSI)			SONY

@{UNDERLINED "Reported @{BOLD "NOT"} to work on:"}
Sanyo drives				(SCSI and ATAPI)
Overdrive/Zappo				(ATAPI?)
Mitsumi	FX series			(ATAPI)
Wearnes					(ATAPI)
Teac					(ATAPI)

And all drives that are accessed thru cd.device command mode

If your CD drive is not in one of these two lists, tell it to me !
@ENDNODE

@NODE PREFS "Preferences page"
@TOC GUI
@{PARI -4}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{BOLD "Device"}@{LINE}
Put here the device of your CDROM controler. Default is "scsi.device".@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Unit"}@{LINE}
Choose here the unit of your CDROM. Default is unit 1.@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Mem type"}@{LINE}
Allow you to choose the type of memory your controller need for sampling.@{LINE}@{I}
0   = ANY@{LINE}
1   = PUBLIC@{LINE}
2   = CHIP@{LINE}
4   = FAST@{LINE}
512 = 24BITDMA@{LINE}@{UI}
If you want, for example, FAST PUBLIC memory use 5 (4+1)@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Play16"}@{LINE}
This is the path that OptyCDPlayer will use for running play16 when it needs
to play the sample.@{LINE}
Default is "c:".@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Disks"}@{LINE}
This is the path that OptyCDPlayer will use for searching disk id files.@{LINE}
Default is "progdir:disks".@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Gadgets"}@{LINE}
This is the path that OptyCDPlayer will use for finding its gadgets (Play,
Eject, ...).@{LINE}
That permit you to use your own gadgets.@{LINE}
Default is "Progdir:Gadgets/Default".@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Intro Time"}@{LINE}
The time played for each title in introscan mode@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Voltype"}@{LINE}
The volume type supported by your CD drive. Ranged from 0 to 3. 0 means soft
volume disabled. Default is 1 (normal use)@{LINE}
If the volume still don't work, it's because your CD drive can't support
Software modifications of the volume... Sorry@{LINE}
This slider has no effect with CD32 command mode.@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Async Buffer"}@{LINE}
The size of the asynchronous write buffer default is 4096 (should work in most
case but slow down sampling). 2048 is the minimum. If a lower value
is selected then non buffered write functions will be used instead...@{LINE}
It has been added because of some problem encountered with cpu-sucker
controllers. Before, a buffer of 307200 bytes (75*4096) was used but it's only
worked if the cpu was not overloaded with the CD drive controller or by other
tasks !@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Filenote"}@{LINE}
Enable or disable the possibility to add filenote with disk files
Warning: filenotes (file comments) significantly slow down DCFS !@{LINE}
Default to ON.@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "YACDP"}@{LINE}
If enabled the filename format used for saving diskfiles is YACDP instead of
MCDPlayer. This option does *not* affect in any way the filename recognition,
to say that MCDplayer filename is still checked when inserting a CD, and vice
versa.@{LINE}
Default to OFF.@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Rezero"}@{LINE}
Some Drives don't like the normal stop command, rezero_unit command can be
used instead with this.@{LINE}
Default to OFF@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Time"}@{LINE}
Use this when you get a bad diplay count for playing time or when Rewind and
Forward don't work.@{LINE}
Default to OFF@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "CD32 Emulation"}@{LINE}
Enable the "cd.device" (originally made for CDł˛) command mode. Be careful,
you must only enable this mode if your device can not handle SCSI commands,
otherwise this could lead to severe crashes!@{LINE}
@{UNDERLINED "Note for Atapi_pnp300 cd.device owners"}:@{LINE}
your device can work @{BOLD "with or without"} this mode enabled but I recommend you
@{BOLD "not"} to enable it, because sampling can't be made, as far as I know, thru
cd.device command mode!@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{PARI 0}
@{LINDENT 0}
The 'keys' group is for shortkeys of the main buttons of the player.@{PAR}
These shortcuts are global to the CDplayer (valids at any page)@{PAR}
@{PARI -4}
@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Prv"} (previous track)@{LINE}
Default: F1@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Fwd"} (fast rewind)@{LINE}
Default: F2@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Play"}@{LINE}
Default: F3@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Stop"}@{LINE}
Default: F4@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Fwd"} (fast forward)@{LINE}
Default: F5@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Nxt"} (next track)@{LINE}
Default: F6@{LINE}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "Eject"}@{LINE}
Default: F7@{LINE}
@{PAR}
all is saved when selecting Prefs/Save in the menu.@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Rexx "Rexx interface"
@TOC Main
OptyCDPlayer has a minimal Rexx interface because it is not meant to be a
'rexxcd' replacement. Anyway the commands set actually available should be
enough for CD control with SCALA or equivalent...@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
 @{U}                                                                                    @{UU}
|@{U}@{B}Command@{UB}     |@{B}Template@{UB}                   |@{B}Description@{UB}                    |@{B}Return code@{UB}@{UU}|
|@{U}quit        |FORCE/S                    |force to quit optycdplayer     |none       @{UU}|
|@{U}hide        |                           |iconify                        |none       @{UU}|
|@{U}deactivate  |                           |iconify                        |none       @{UU}|
|@{U}show        |                           |uniconify                      |none       @{UU}|
|@{U}activate    |                           |uniconify                      |none       @{UU}|
|info        |ITEM/A                     |give info about an MUI item    |none       |
|@{U}            |                           |(see script example)           |           @{UU}|
|help        |FILE/A                     |give list of commands and      |none       |
|@{U}            |                           |templates                      |           @{UU}|
|playtrack   |T=TRACK/A/N,O=OFFSET/A/N,  |play track T from O secs       |0=success  |
|@{U}            |D=DURATION/A/N             |during D secs                  |           @{UU}|
|jump        |S=SECONDS/A/N              |jump S secs ahead              |0=success  |
|@{U}            |                           |(or back with a neg value)     |           @{UU}|
|previous    |                           |go to start of track or        |0=success  |
|@{U}            |                           |previous track                 |           @{UU}|
|playpause   |                           |start playing or go into       |0=success  |
|@{U}            |                           |pause if already playing       |           @{UU}|
|@{U}next        |                           |go to next track               |0=success  @{UU}|
|@{U}eject       |                           |eject (no need to stop before) |0=success  @{UU}|
|@{U}stop        |                           |stop playing                   |0=success  @{UU}|
|status      |                           |get status of the player       |0=NoDisk,  |
|            |                           |                               |1=Playing, |
|            |                           |                               |2=Stopped, |
|            |                           |                               |3=Paused,  |
|@{U}            |                           |                               |4=Datadisk @{UU}|
@ENDNODE

@NODE Bugs "Bugs"
@TOC Main
@{PARI -2}
@{LINDENT 2}
- Some devices refuses CDDA already in them when first opened, they complain
that the device can't be opened!@{PAR}
  @{UNDERLINED "NOTE"}: This is a bug from the device file on which the drive is!@{PAR}
@{PAR}
- The software Volume don't work with some CD drives@{PAR}
@{PAR}
- The CD Database contains a few strange CD ids that was not generated by my
CDs nor my CDdrive, I don't know if it's really good to keep them...@{PAR}
@{PAR}
- I figured out that there is some drives that give different results about
track duration each time the same CD is inserted (!)@{PAR}
@{PAR}
- The application often hangs while changing (with the balance gadget) the
playgroup weight. This is a bug from MUI and I will try to find a workaround
for future versions of OptyCDPlayer (unless this bug is removed)@{PAR}
@{PAR}
Send bugreports at @{BOLD "opty@netinfo.fr"}@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Future "Future"
@TOC Main
- more catalog files@{PAR}
- Suggestions ?@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"
@TOC Main
@{PARI -1}
@{LINDENT 1}
@{BOLD "- V1.0 (Jun-96)"}@{PAR}
·Initial public release.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.1 (Jun-96)"}@{PAR}
·VOLTYPE tooltype added to correct problems with some exotic CD drives.@{PAR}
·Added 600(!) CD descriptions.@{PAR}
·German catalog added.@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.2 (Jul-96)"}@{PAR}
·Icons was in Newicon style, now they are real icons@{PAR}
·Rewritten some functions in assembler@{PAR}
·Reduced code size significantly@{PAR}
·Added MUI Gadget disappearing feature: when the window is too small, some
gadgets start to disappear according to their importance@{PAR}
·Added possibility to choose the sample file by requester@{PAR}
·Added preview button in sampler window, it plays CD according sliders of the
sampler window@{PAR}
·Rewritten randomize function (more randomized)@{PAR}
·Editor,Program, & sampler pages are allocated only when needed. Replacing
Register style with a Cycle was necessary for this feature.@{PAR}
·Fixed stupid bug with 'at start' prog: first title was played twice@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.3 (Jul-96)"}@{PAR}
·Now there is 1368 CD descriptions@{PAR}
·Added ASYNCBUFFER to suppress glitches when sampling@{PAR}
·Removed some scsi command failure check at initialisation and termination of
sampling function because of some drive that can but refuse these command anyway.@{PAR}
·Added my E-Mail address in 'About' window (Requested)@{PAR}
·Added config autosave, some tooltypes are now obsolete, please remove
SAMPLENAME, DRIVETYPE, SAMPLEFORMAT, SAMPLECHANNEL, SAMPLEFREQ from your icon@{PAR}
·Added Drive Subcode in prefs@{PAR}
·Added Volume prefs. Note that volume is not initialized anymore to 127 at
each start except if no config (first start)@{PAR}
·Added slider in player part for fast search in song@{PAR}
·Finally, as suggested by a lot of users, I have added possibility to put disk
descriptions in a Database, mainly because the little cd description files are
very diskspace consuming. But be careful, as it's an archive database style, I
have splitted it in many files for faster access. BTW, if HD space doesn't
really matter for you, old format is still recognized (load,save,...) and will
never be removed as it's a standard...@{PAR}
·Added button for 'Disk to DataBase' conversion@{PAR}
·Added button for 'DataBase to Disk' conversion@{PAR}
·Added gauge progression for DataBase manipulation and Sample save@{PAR}
·Added BUFMEMTYPE for DMA controllers, value: 0=ANY, 512=24BITDMA, ...@{PAR}
·Added possibility to ear *in real time* the sampling preview/process thru the
amiga audio channels. The replay is always 8 bits even if 16 bits save was
selected but you can play at 44.1khz if you have a screenmode with horizontal
freq >15khz, so if you use OptyCD on a PAL or NTSC screen, don't try 44100 !
Keep in mind that this mode is very cpu consuming and will give bad result on
low powered system since sampling can only be done at ~150 k/s. By the way,
you will notice that channel are not always synchronised, it's because I don't
know how to sync the 4 voices. Anybody can help me ?@{PAR}
·Added cycle and pref saving of the output mode (in sampling part)@{PAR}
·Added icons from Rudy Top@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.4 (Jul-96)"}@{PAR}
·Included greek catalog@{PAR}
·Included finnish catalog@{PAR}
·Catalog description is now compatible with catedit@{PAR}
·Included italian catalog@{PAR}
·Added DISKIDPATH to specify the path for disk id files@{PAR}
·Fixed VOLTYPE, It was not activated...@{PAR}
·Now value outside 1..3 range for VOLTYPE mean software volume disabled@{PAR}
·Removed this ugly Eject lock, I found a workaround to detect 'hard' insertion
and ejection while using my special routine for universal CDDA autodetection.
In fact, only CD drive that continue to give CD directory of the last ejected
CD will still have some problems...@{PAR}
·Removed skip track bug introduced with fast search bar@{PAR}
·Now, 'Repeat All' works for programs too@{PAR}
·Possibility to make 'repeat' the 'random' mode (Random must be selected
first)@{PAR}
·Now 'Start Prog' start at launch of program AND at CD insertion too@{PAR}
·The documentation is now in AmigaGuide format@{PAR}
·OptyCDPlayer should now work (specially programs) iconified, even when
started iconified@{PAR}
·Found a way to synchronize Amiga voices, there should be no more distortion@{PAR}
·It is now *really* possible to insert a disk with player page not the active
one@{PAR}
·Math ieee library for AIFF not more needed...@{PAR}
·Possibility to start Random while playing (will be randomized at the next
track played)@{PAR}
·Now if ASYNCBUFFER as a value lower than 2048 then synchronous write will be
used@{PAR}
·Database now contains 1389 CD descriptions@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.5 (Aug-96)"}@{PAR}
·If VOLTYPE is equal to 0 then there is no volume button@{PAR}
·Added "Project" menu with "About", "About MUI", and "Quit"@{PAR}
·About button has been removed@{PAR}
·Added "Preferences" menu with "Save", and "MUI"@{PAR}
·Player configuration saving is not made at the end of program anymore, please
use Preferences/Save menu to save config@{PAR}
·"Introscan" & "Random" gadgets are now checkmark type gadgets@{PAR}
·"Repeat" is now a cycle gadget@{PAR}
·All combinations between Repeat, Introscan, and Random should now be possible@{PAR}
·"A-B" button changed@{PAR}
·Optimized a little bit the sampling routine@{PAR}
·Added Atapi sampling command, please report me if you drive works with it
(try it even if it's an SCSI...)@{PAR}
·Status bar removed and replaced by graphical items@{PAR}
·The first page of the player now react to up/down keys, they play next/prev
title in the list by changing the list active title@{PAR}
·Play/Stop/Next/Previous/Forward/Rewind/Eject commands react to shortkeys
defined by tooltypes (see tooltypes part).@{PAR}
·Changed a little bit the .guide location for online help and multiple
translations@{PAR}
·Included Danish catalog and documentation@{PAR}
·Added DiskNote.rexx (c) by Niels Bache@{PAR}
·Added FILENOTE tooltype to add filecomment with diskfiles when saved@{PAR}
·Database now contains 1499 CD descriptions@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.6 (Sep-96)"}@{PAR}
·IFF8SVX STEREO saving should now works with Amiga output activated@{PAR}
·Included Polish catalog@{PAR}
·Updated Italian catalog@{PAR}
·Updated German catalog@{PAR}
·Updated Norvegian catalog@{PAR}
·Updated Finnish catalog@{PAR}
·Fixed a bug while saving 8bits with Output switched to CD@{PAR}
·Added Italian guide@{PAR}
·New Disknote.rexx@{PAR}
·Repeat, Random, and IntroScan now reflect the config correctly@{PAR}
·Added capability to configure position of gadget groups at the player page by
using 'Preferences/Edit Mode' menuitem and drag&drop.@{PAR}
·Now OptyCDPlayer test if it's a real CDRom drive on the selected unit@{PAR}
·Reworked the guide a little bit@{PAR}
·Included more informations about me@{PAR}
·Included Swedish catalog@{PAR}
·Database now contains 2464 CD descriptions@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.7 (Oct-96)"} (Not Released!)@{PAR}
·Forgot to mention for the precedent version that the sampling routine has
been a little bit modified in the expectation of more tolerance with some
drives, unfortunately this significantly slow down the sampling...@{PAR}
·Asynchronous write routine enhanced@{PAR}
·Removed Disknote.rexx (obsolete, use FILENOTE tooltype instead)@{PAR}
·Added support for YACDP diskfiles format (see YACDP tooltype), unfortunately
there is no possibility to convert from this format to MCD format or the
database format excepted when the corresponding CD is inserted, to say that
'YACDPDisks->DB' and 'DB->YACDPDisks' can't be made.@{PAR}
·Added in the About window the number of CDs contained in the database@{PAR}
·Forgot to close Catalog file at exit@{PAR}
·Added function to merge 2 DataBases (TitleEditor/MergeDB)@{PAR}
·Added Database viewer (TitleEditor/DBViewer)@{PAR}
·Added STOP Tooltype for stop command alternative@{PAR}
·Added INVERTEDTIME Tooltype for those who don't have a correct time count@{PAR}
·Removed Subcode choice in Sampling part because I got no report about value
other than zero@{PAR}
·Added GADGETPATH tooltype, now you're able to use your own gadgets for Play,
Eject, Stop, ...@{PAR}
·Added "Tiny" gadgets (use GADGETPATH=progdir:gadgets/tiny)@{PAR}
·Added full support for "cd.device" from commodore, but this device has some
severe limitations:@{PAR}
 .Playing must be stopped when exiting@{PAR}
 .Sampling is not supported@{PAR}
 .Can't do my hack for controllers that ignore diskchanges (like mine)@{PAR}
 .Volume is global (no balance)@{PAR}
 .Can't verify the device type due to a big bug in the squirrel/cd.device
  CD_GETGEOMETRY command!@{PAR}
 Use CDDEVICE tooltype to activate it@{PAR}
·Added time field in the title lists@{PAR}
·Lists are now NLists (with horizontal scrollbar)@{PAR}
·Playlist weight is now saved in prefs@{PAR}
·Database contains 2518 CD descriptions@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{BOLD "- V1.8 (Nov-96)"}@{PAR}
·All tooltypes options can now be configured thru the new preferences page@{PAR}
·Error messages are displayed in requester wherever possible@{PAR}
·Player can be started even with an unvalid device, in this case it
automatically switch to the preference page@{PAR}
·Preferences can be changed at run time@{PAR}
·Removed ALL tooltypes because they are not more needed@{PAR}
·Added german guide@{PAR}
·Fixed path bug with play16@{PAR}
·Now, when pressing play button, and there is an active track in the list,
playing will be started at this track@{PAR}
·Data tracks are shown in a different way in the lists@{PAR}
·Added AREXX interface@{PAR}
·Entirely reworked this guide, added smartwrapping, indentation, fx, ...
 Should still render well with 2.0 but not (yet) with HTDS!@{PAR}
·Added AREXX script examples@{PAR}
·ShortKeys are now possible (thru catalogs) with buttons and togglebuttons@{PAR}
·Added slovak catalog@{PAR}
·Database contains 2525 CD descriptions@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

